+# Round-11 baton: DropInsertion native activation — Blocker B FIXED, the FLIP is ready (pending a quiet-window basic sweep)
+
+## Status after round-10
+Round-10 ROOT-CAUSED and FIXED **Blocker B** (the `while True: …; if c: break`
+reachable-empty-block native-codegen blocker) — landed DORMANT-SAFE on branch
+`round10-blocker-b-loop-polarity-fix`, commit `13ecbdb16` (NOT pushed; detached
+worktree branch — the main session should cherry-pick / fast-forward it onto
+main).
+
+### What Blocker B actually was (the round-10 baton's "after_block" framing was right, the layer was lowering)
+NOT a native-codegen block-fill bug. The orphan `after_block` is a SYMPTOM. The
+root cause is in `tir/lower_to_simple.rs`: the structured-loop reconstruction
+chose body_entry/exit_block from the stale `loop_break_kinds` polarity hint.
+molt double-roundtrips through TIR (per-function pipeline lifts SimpleIR→TIR→
+SimpleIR, then the RC drop module phase relifts that SimpleIR→TIR→SimpleIR). The
+SSA terminator builder's `loop_break_if_false` then/else convention + the drop
+phase's back-edge reshaping flip which cond successor is the back-edge body, so
+the recorded hint goes STALE vs the TIR the FINAL lowering sees. For `while True:`
++ inner break, the post-drop cond block is `CondBranch { then: <exit/Return>,
+else: <back-edge/continue> }` but `BreakIfFalse` made the lowering take `then`
+(the EXIT) as the body → empty structured body (all Return → deferred) → the
+`loop_end` that fills `after_block` is dropped → reachable-but-empty `after_block`
+→ Cranelift `unreachable_code.rs:29` `unwrap() on None`.
+
+### The fix (two layers, both in `13ecbdb16`)
+1. **Root cause** (`lower_to_simple.rs`): derive body/exit polarity from the CFG
+   (reducibility) via new `successor_reaches_header(func, start, header, cond)`
+   — the BODY is the cond successor that reaches the loop header (back-edge); the
+   EXIT is the other. body_entry/exit_block AND the emitted `loop_break_if_*`
+   polarity both come from that CFG fact. Stale hint used only as a tie-break for
+   genuinely-ambiguous CFGs (both/neither reach header). Byte-identical for
+   well-formed loops (`concat_while` still emits loop_break_if_false+loop_continue
+   +loop_end).
+2. **Defense-in-depth** (`function_compiler.rs`, the single block-finalization
+   authority, ~line 24890): fail-loud assert that no entry-DFS-reachable block is
+   left empty. Converts any future regression of this class into an actionable
+   molt diagnostic instead of an opaque Cranelift panic. Verified it does NOT
+   fire on the dormant build or the drops-ON memory set.
+
+### Verification (all green — see commit body for the full table)
+- design-20 memory set: **14/14 byte-identical with native drops ON** (was 13/14,
+  Blocker B was the lone failure); **16/16 byte-identical DORMANT** (14 + the
+  round-9 & round-10 regressions), MOLT_VERIFY_ANALYSIS=1 clean, assertion silent.
+- `rc_sites_loop_break.py` drops-ON: zero panics, output 1000000, RSS plateau
+  8 MiB (matches the protocol's "concat ≈9MiB" target).
+- NEW regression `tests/differential/basic/loop_while_true_break_drops.py`
+  (single/double/value-carrying/heap-condition breaks) byte-identical, drops ON
+  and dormant. June-3 double-break class HEALED.
+- Rust gates (committed dormant state): native lib 1023/0, native+llvm lib
+  1092/0, runtime lib 510/0 (+16 ignored), clippy -D warnings clean ×2, final
+  release-fast dormant build clean.
+
+## WHY THE FLIP IS STILL HELD (the ONLY remaining gate)
+The native flip (`pass_manager.rs` `target_uses_tir_drop_insertion`
+NativeCranelift => true) needs a clean full `tests/differential/basic` (807
+tests) sweep against the calibration oracle (`tests/molt_diff.py`) in a QUIET
+window. Round-10 could NOT run it: the host was under heavy multi-agent
+contention (sessions `shiftfix`, `asyncfix`, codex companions all building/
+testing concurrently). The differential harness was SIGKILLed repeatedly
+(`exit 144`) — both the full `molt_diff.py` run and an ad-hoc scoped raw-cmp
+sweep died mid-run to host-pressure SIGKILLs, NOT to any defect. The flip
+protocol ALSO requires quiet-window perf medians (bench_counter_words==97360,
+bench_calls ≈ dormant, no perf regression), which contention makes meaningless.
+This is operational, not a code blocker — Blocker B is genuinely fixed.
+
+## What round-11 must do (THE FLIP — de-risked, the hard structural work is done)
+1. In a QUIET window (`molt clean --apply --kill-processes` first; confirm
+   `pgrep -fl 'cargo build|cargo check'` == 0 and ≥80% mem free), fast-forward
+   `13ecbdb16` onto main (or cherry-pick the 3 files; it is dormant-safe so it can
+   land independently of the flip).
+2. Temp-wire `target_uses_tir_drop_insertion` NativeCranelift => true, rebuild
+   (FOREGROUND `cargo build --profile release-fast -p molt-backend --features
+   native-backend` with a long timeout — see OPS below; the `nohup bash -c '(...)'`
+   pattern died silently every time under contention this round).
+3. Run the full basic sweep: `python3 tests/molt_diff.py tests/differential/basic
+   --jobs 4 --warm-cache --json-output …` (jobs 3-4 native-only; the baton's
+   "jobs 2 OOMs" caveat is for the llvm-feature binary). Re-verify any failure in
+   isolation with `MOLT_BACKEND_DAEMON=0` before attributing to drops — the
+   harness rebuild gets SIGKILLed under any sibling load, masking the real RC.
+4. ZERO drops-caused failures → flip `=> true` FOR REAL + full gates (cargo test
+   both feature sets + runtime, clippy ×2, MOLT_VERIFY_ANALYSIS=1, design-20 ×3
+   lanes, compliance serial, honesty guard + ratchet removals for anything the
+   flip fixes), perf table no-regression with quiet-window medians, RSS plateaus
+   (concat ≈9MiB, list(range) 17-24MiB, bigint ≈8MiB). Evidence in the commit.
+5. NEW drops-caused class appears in the sweep → STOP, triage precisely
+   (round-12), land any reconstruction/codegen fix dormant-safe. The compile
+   dies on the first such class, so the full count past Blocker B is still unknown
+   (the baton's standing caveat). Blocker B was the first the memory set exposed;
+   the 807-test basic surface may expose more.
+
+## Blocker C (WASM repr, #59 family) — STILL NOT a native gate, do not chase for the flip
+The heavy-module WASM stress (`import typing/re/collections/json/dataclasses/
+functools/itertools/textwrap`) fails WASM structural validation
+(`func N … expected i64 but nothing on stack`) — a LIR i64/DynBox repr class in
+`lower_to_lir`/`repr_by_value`→`LirRepr`, independent of the native flip and of
+round-10's lowering fix (native is byte-identical on those shapes). Round-10's
+fix shares `lower_to_simple_ir` with WASM and improves the swapped-polarity
+shape for WASM too, but does not touch the repr/stack class. Separate arc.
+
+## OPS hazards that cost round-10 real time (reuse these)
+- **`nohup bash -c '(cargo build … ; echo RC=$? > rc)'` DIES SILENTLY under host
+  contention** — no rustc, no rc, log frozen at "Compiling molt-backend". Every
+  backgrounded build that started while a partner build held the cargo registry
+  lock died this way. FIX: run the backend build in the FOREGROUND with a long
+  `timeout` (the Bash tool's `timeout: 400000` + `dangerouslyDisableSandbox:
+  true`); it finished in 36-57s reliably. Reserve backgrounding for the long
+  test SWEEP, not the build.
+- **`molt clean --apply --kill-processes` nukes the worktree's session target
+  dir AND `tmp/`** — it removed `target-round10/release-fast/molt-backend` and the
+  `tmp/round10/*.py` repros mid-session, forcing a full backend rebuild. Do NOT
+  run it mid-session against a worktree you are actively building in; only at the
+  very end. Keep repros OUTSIDE `tmp/` (which is a repo artifact dir clean wipes).
+- **`molt_diff.py` defaults to the `dev`/`dev-fast` profile**, so it builds a
+  SEPARATE `target-round10/dev-fast/molt-backend` from source — it WILL pick up a
+  source temp-flip, but it is a different binary than your `release-fast` one.
+  Warm/verify the profile you intend to test.
+- The differential harness (and any heavy multi-build loop) is SIGKILLed under
+  sibling-agent load (`exit 144`). cmp -s for verdicts (rtk diff lies). Stale
+  backend daemons print their last-log (including a prior panic) before a fresh
+  daemon takes over — a panic line in `molt build` output is NOT proof the
+  CURRENT binary panicked; confirm with `MOLT_BACKEND_DAEMON=0` + `panics=0`.
+
+## Recovery pointers (round-10 work, on branch round10-blocker-b-loop-polarity-fix)
+- The fix: `runtime/molt-backend/src/tir/lower_to_simple.rs`
+  (`successor_reaches_header` + the body_is_then derivation at the loop-region
+  detection ~line 573) and `runtime/molt-backend/src/native_backend/
+  function_compiler.rs` (the finalization assertion ~line 24890).
+- The regression: `tests/differential/basic/loop_while_true_break_drops.py`
+  (CPython output: `1 50 1 50 2 119 'aaaa' 'aaaaaaa'`).
+- Debug recipe that nailed it: `MOLT_DEBUG_DROP=ALL` (post-drop TIR) +
+  `MOLT_DUMP_FINAL_FUNC_IR=<fn>` (final SimpleIR op stream — the smoking gun was
+  `loop_start`+`loop_break_if_false` with NO `loop_end`) + `MOLT_DEBUG_LOWER_FUNC=
+  <full_fn_name>` (`LOWER_DEBUG_REGION` shows break_kind/body_entry/exit_block) +
+  `MOLT_DUMP_CLIF_FUNC=<fn>` (the empty `block11:` at the function tail).
